# Walkthrough - Scout DB UI Refinements

This walkthrough documents the UI/UX improvements made to the Vulnerability Overrides section of Scout DB.

## Redundant Element Removal & Header Streamlining

I have streamlined the "Create Override" interface by removing redundant headers and cards, significantly reducing the vertical footprint.

- **Removed `SheetHeader`**: Eliminated the redundant "Create New Override" title and description from the drawer component.
- **Removed [OverrideForm](file:///c:/SCOUTNEW/scout_db/frontend/src/pages/Overrides/OverrideForm.tsx#9-167) Header**: Removed the second "Create Override" title/description within the form itself.
- **Removed Summary Card**: Integrated the vulnerability ID directly into the edit form header for a cleaner look.

